{
  "id": "RLSA-2026:28143",
  "title": "Important: postgresql:16 security update",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-06-23 12:01:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-07-07 12:06:36"
  },
  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "PostgreSQL is an advanced object-relational database management system (DBMS).\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* postgresql: PostgreSQL: Credential recovery via covert timing channel in MD5 password comparison (CVE-2026-6478)\n\n* postgresql: integer overflow can cause an undersized allocation and an out-of-bounds write (CVE-2026-6473)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
